    <h1 id="title">Pat Tillman</h1>
    <div id="img-div">
      <img id="image" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Pat_Tillman.jpg/440px-Pat_Tillman.jpg" alt="Pat Tillman">
      <figcaption id="img-caption">Pat Tillman, former NFL player who left his sports career to serve in the U.S. Army and tragically lost his life in Afghanistan.</figcaption>
    </div>
    <div id="tribute-info">
      <p>Pat Tillman was an American professional football player and U.S. Army Ranger. He left a promising NFL career to serve his country in the wake of the September 11 attacks. Pat's legacy continues to inspire many through his selfless actions and dedication to duty.</p>
      <p>Born in 1976, Pat Tillman played college football for Arizona State University before being drafted by the Arizona Cardinals. His decision to enlist in the U.S. Army in 2002, after the September 11 attacks, reflected his deep sense of patriotism and commitment to serving a greater cause.</p>
      <p>Pat Tillman was killed in action on April 22, 2004, in Afghanistan. His life and legacy continue to be honored through the Pat Tillman Foundation, which provides scholarships and resources for military veterans and their families.</p>
    </div>
    <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pat_Tillman" target="_blank">Learn more about Pat Tillman</a>
